Frontend (What Users See & Touch)

Studio.holoscript.net — browser-only, no install. English → node graph → live WebXR preview. Usable? Yeah, kinda. You can prompt "grabbable glowing crystal" and watch it spin in VR. But it's shallow: 50 scenarios, basic traits (@physics, @haptic), no deep collab or multiplayer yet. Feels like a tech demo, not a creator hub.
IDE integrations (VS Code, IntelliJ, etc.) — LSP/debugger exist, agents suggest code, but docs are thin. No "extension marketplace" vibe like VS Code—it's just "use our CLI" and pray.
