Backend (The Real Engine)

Compiler — 16 backends, 25 targets (Unity, Godot, visionOS, ROS, OpenUSD...). Incremental builds, circuit breakers. Sounds killer—compile once, ship everywhere. Usable? Partially. WebGPU/WebXR exports work fine, OpenUSD/URDF too. But "16 named backends"? No list, no code samples, no reliability proof. Is it stable on Roblox Luau? Who knows—docs ghosted.
Runtime — Three.js browser, Rust WebGPU. Local-first, zero-cloud. But no clear "how to deploy native" guide. You get a .holo file → magic happens? Or crash?
MCP (3-layer comms) — RealTime/A2A/MCP for agents. This is the secret sauce—swarm orchestration, HITL gates. But zero public spec. No flow diagram. No "here's how agents talk" example. Feels like black-box hype.
OpenClaw — Your local agent swarm. Ties to Brittney/Ollama. Autonomous scene gen? Cool in theory. But 2026 OpenClaw hype is everywhere—people building test agents, parallel subs—but HoloScript's version? Barely mentioned outside your posts. Is it forked? Custom? Docs say nothing.

